theorem Topology.P3_iInter_closed_finite
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Type _} [Fintype ι]
    {F : ι → Set X} (hClosed : ∀ i, IsClosed (F i))
    (hP3 : ∀ i, Topology.P3 (F i)) :
    Topology.P3 (⋂ i, F i) := by
  -- Each closed set satisfying `P3` is open.
  have hOpenF : ∀ i, IsOpen (F i) := by
    intro i
    have : IsOpen (F i) :=
      (Topology.P3_closed_iff_isOpen (A := F i) (hClosed i)).1 (hP3 i)
    exact this
  -- The finite intersection of the open sets `F i` is open.
  have hOpenInter : IsOpen (⋂ i, F i) := by
    simpa using isOpen_iInter hOpenF
  -- Every open set satisfies `P3`.
  exact (Topology.IsOpen_P1_and_P3 (A := ⋂ i, F i) hOpenInter).2
